---
import AcademyLayout from '../../layouts/AcademyLayout.astro';
---

<AcademyLayout
  title="Summer 2026 Program Series — Nguyen AI Edu"
  description="Summer 2026: learn AI, build a capability portfolio, find work, freelance and start up with Nguyen AI Edu. Online nationwide, in-person in Da Lat."
  activeNav="home"
>
  <section class="academy-container py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-academy-text mb-4">
        Summer 2026: learn for real, do for real, open a new path
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-academy-muted">
        A program series by Nguyen AI Edu for students, young people and anyone who wants to change their career path
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-academy">
      <p>
        In summer 2026, Nguyen AI Edu opens a program series for young people standing at a crossroads: about to graduate, recently graduated, looking for work, wanting to change careers, or simply wanting to learn something genuinely useful.
      </p>

      <p>
        The program runs online, open to every province and city. When conditions allow, we organize in-person activities in Da Lat, Lam Dong — where learners meet, work in teams and build products in a creative environment.
      </p>

      <p>
        We prioritize those who carry the Nguyen surname, but the program is open to anyone who fits — anyone with a serious learning spirit, a love of technology, a love of creativity, and a desire to create real value for themselves and their community.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Why this program exists</h2>

      <p>
        Many students graduate with a degree in hand but do not know where to start. They have studied a lot, but lack a real capability portfolio. They want to work but have no experience. They want part-time work but do not know which job to choose — one that both pays and develops skills. They want to start a business but the direction is unclear, the product does not exist, the customers are unknown. They want to use AI but do not know how to use it correctly, usefully, and to produce results.
      </p>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu was built for that group of people.
      </p>

      <p>
        We believe learning must come with practice. Practice must produce a product. A product must have evidence. Evidence must open up opportunities — employment, part-time work, a startup, or a new career path.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Who the program is for</h2>

      <p>
        If you are a final-year student, a recent graduate, a young person looking for work, someone who wants part-time work this summer, someone who wants to change career direction, someone who wants to learn more about AI, someone who wants to build a personal brand, someone who wants to start a small business, or someone who wants to join a technology, education, media or business project — this program is for you.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you love Da Lat and want to join in-person experiences when scheduled, or you carry the Nguyen surname and want to contribute to a learning, working and startup ecosystem with character — you are also welcome.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Priority age range:</strong> 20–49, especially students, new workers and young people looking for career change opportunities.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Eight focus areas</h2>

      <h3>1. AI for learning and work</h3>
      <p>
        Learn how to use artificial intelligence to learn faster, research better, write more clearly, plan more solidly. The goal is not to use tools for fun — it is to produce verifiable results.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Capability portfolio and job search</h3>
      <p>
        Build a personal profile, position your capabilities, describe your experience, prepare sample products. Present your capabilities in a way that employers, partners and customers can understand.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Part-time work and project-based internships</h3>
      <p>
        Aim for part-time jobs with long-term development value: content support, media, research, project assistance, learning operations, business support, verified data entry. Anything that can be done online is fair game.
      </p>

      <h3>4. Content creation and personal brand</h3>
      <p>
        Build your personal voice, choose content topics, plan a posting schedule, tell your career story. Use content to open up learning, work, collaboration or startup opportunities.
      </p>

      <h3>5. Local brand and national brand</h3>
      <p>
        Prioritize ideas tied to local communities: native products, culture, tourism, agriculture, education. Vietnamese values that can be developed into sustainable brands.
      </p>

      <h3>6. Small startups and digital business</h3>
      <p>
        Startup thinking from the basics: identify a problem, understand customers, design a product, test the market, build a landing page, create content, set prices, sell on a trial basis, improve.
      </p>

      <h3>7. Investment, sponsorship and development opportunities</h3>
      <p>
        Foundational knowledge about investment, sponsorship, fundraising, scholarships, responsibility to sponsors and how to present a valuable idea. This is educational and orientational content, not a financial investment invitation.
      </p>

      <h3>8. Self-determined work</h3>
      <p>
        The ultimate goal: help learners gradually become able to self-learn, self-do, self-build a portfolio, self-create products, self-find opportunities and self-take responsibility for their own path.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Learning format</h2>

      <h3>Online, open nationwide</h3>
      <p>
        Join from any province or city. Content suits students on summer break, recent graduates, working people or anyone who wants to learn more outside working hours.
      </p>

      <h3>In-person experience in Da Lat</h3>
      <p>
        When conditions allow, Nguyen AI Edu opens in-person activities in Da Lat, Lam Dong. Meet experts, work in teams, join real projects, practice presentation skills and build products in a creative environment.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>July 2026 scholarships</h2>

      <p>
        In July 2026, Nguyen AI Edu plans to prioritize the first 11 scholarships for each program group. Scholarships are for early registrants with clear goals, a serious learning spirit and readiness to produce a real product after the learning process.
      </p>

      <p><strong>Priority for:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>people who carry the Nguyen surname;</li>
        <li>final-year students and recent graduates;</li>
        <li>young people looking for work;</li>
        <li>people in circumstances that need support;</li>
        <li>people who love AI and startups;</li>
        <li>people who want to develop a local brand, community or personal project;</li>
        <li>people who commit to completing lessons, tests, practice and a final product.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        After the 11 scholarships in July 2026 are filled, learners can choose a free program (if still open), a partially supported program, paid courses on edu.nguyenai.net, or more in-depth programs when conditions allow. Early registrants are reviewed first.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>An important clarification</h2>

      <div class="p-4 bg-academy-header rounded-lg border border-academy-border my-6">
        <p class="text-academy-text">
          This is a learning and practice program, not a promise of employment, fundraising or startup success. Outcomes depend on the seriousness, capability and effort of each learner.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        What the program commits to within its ability: create a learning, practice, orientation, feedback and support environment so that learners have the opportunity to build real capability. Learners who want to go far need to take responsibility for themselves — study fully, do the work, correct mistakes, practice, create products, submit evidence and complete their capability portfolio.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>What learners have after the program</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on the learning group, learners are oriented to produce one or more results: a personal capability portfolio, a career plan, content products, a personal or project landing page, a clearly presented startup idea, a job search or part-time work plan, a small verifiable project, a better application portfolio, the ability to use AI in learning and work, and direction for building a personal, local or community brand.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Who should register early</h2>

      <p>
        You should register early if you are about to graduate, just graduated but unsure of your direction, want to learn more in summer 2026, want part-time work but not just short-term jobs that do not develop skills, want to use AI in learning and work, want to build a personal brand, want to start a small business, want to join a community of learners and doers with direction, or want a chance to receive a scholarship before spots run out.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Register</h2>

      <div class="my-6 p-6 bg-academy-header rounded-lg border border-academy-border">
        <a href="/en/apply" class="academy-btn academy-btn-primary text-lg">
          Register now at edu.nguyenai.net
        </a>
      </div>

      <p>
        July 2026 prioritizes early registrants. Priority for those who carry the Nguyen surname, but still open to suitable, serious people who want to create real value.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-lg text-academy-accent font-semibold">
        Nguyen AI Edu welcomes young people who want to learn for real, do for real, create real products and open up a new direction for their future.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <div class="p-4 bg-academy-header rounded-lg border border-academy-border">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-academy-text mb-3">Support contact</h3>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
          <span class="text-academy-accent" aria-hidden="true">&#128241;</span>
          <span>Hotline/Zalo: <a href="tel:0989660750" class="text-academy-accent font-medium hover:underline">0989660750</a></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AcademyLayout>
